12 and services necessary for pupils to participate in sanctioned sports. Section 3
13 additionally: (1) sets forth approved uses for money deposited in the Fund; (2)
14 authorizes the Association to accept gifts, grants and donations from any source for
15 deposit in the Fund; and (3) requires the interest and income earned on the money
16 in the Fund to be credited to the Fund. Finally, section 3 requires the Executive
17 Director of the Association to: (1) prepare an annual report containing certain
18 information concerning the Fund; and (2) submit the report to the Director of the
19 Legislative Counsel Bureau for transmittal to the Joint Interim Standing Committee
20 on Education.
21 Section 4 of this bill requires the Association to conduct a study regarding: (1)
22 the development of pupils as athletes in this State; and (2) the infrastructure
23 required to transform pupils who participate in sanctioned sports into professional
24 athletes. Section 4 additionally sets forth: (1) the required contents of the study; (2)
25 the deadline for completion of the study; and (3) a requirement that a report of the
26 findings of the study be submitted to the Director of the Legislative Counsel Bureau
27 for transmittal to the Joint Interim Standing Committee on Education. Furthermore,
28 section 4: (1) authorizes the Association to request the drafting of not more than 1
29 legislative measure which relates to matters within the scope of the study; and (2)
30 sets forth requirements for the submission of the legislative measure for drafting.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 385B of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto the provisions set forth as sections 2 and 3 of this act.
3 Sec. 2. The Nevada Interscholastic Activities Association
4 shall adopt regulations that designate lacrosse as a sanctioned
5 sport. The regulations adopted pursuant to this section must
6 include, without limitation, provisions:
7 1. Governing the eligibility and participation of pupils;
8 2. Prescribing the rules used in competition;
9 3. Establishing the length of a season of lacrosse and the date
10 upon which a school may begin practicing for a season of
11 lacrosse;
12 4. Establishing guidelines for the safety of pupils that comply
13 with any regulations adopted pursuant to NRS 385B.080; and
14 5. Prescribing any other guidelines necessary to govern
15 participation in lacrosse competitions.
16 Sec. 3. 1. The Nevada Interscholastic Activities Association
17 shall establish a fund to be known as the Pipeline Infrastructure
18 Fund to support the development and management of
19 infrastructure and services necessary for pupils to participate in
20 sanctioned sports, including, without limitation, lacrosse. The
21 Association must use the money deposited in the Fund to:
22 (a) Hire or contract with persons to assist in implementing and
23 managing the growth of athletics programs at schools;
